        "timestamp": 1546635548
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>well mostly I am not sure what the purpose of he README is -- who's expected to go there for which information. it's kind of the \"start page\" on the repo on github, after all</p>",
        "id": 154468641,
        "sender_full_name": "RalfJ",
        "timestamp": 1546684874
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In the short term it seems like it would be reasonable to at least change the \"Build and install\" step into two distinct \"build\" and \"install\" steps, and mark the \"install\" step optional.</p>",
        "id": 157271897,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1548941948
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/57746\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/57746\">#57746</a> did at least add an additional link to the rustc-guide</p>",
        "id": 157271996,
        "sender_full_name": "pnkfelix",
        "timestamp": 1548942028
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so we got <a href=\"https://rust-lang.github.io/rustc-guide/how-to-build-and-run.html\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://rust-lang.github.io/rustc-guide/how-to-build-and-run.html\">https://rust-lang.github.io/rustc-guide/how-to-build-and-run.html</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\">https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md</a> with quite some overlap, it seems?</p>",
